title>   Bushwill clean but not sober</span><hr size=1> After hearing tales of a small island off of qeynos with <br>
Willow Wisps carrying Greater Lightstones I need to turn in<br>
for a research book and resale value I decided it was time<br>
to leave the relative safety of Ak'Anon for the first time. I<br>
stopped in the Nexus to get a disturbingly available KEI and<br>
headed to the docks in qeynos. <br>
I must say although I really enjoyed the voyage I find it<br>
cruel to put a wall of spirits three Gnomes high and ten wide<br>
without a bartender to serve any of it.<br>
Upon arrival on the island in Erud's Crossing I introduced<br>
myself to the locals and was received somewhat warmly. All<br>
the visible life was in fact indifferent to my presence so I<br>
proceeded to summon up an earth elemental, a magical<br>
weapon and shield for him, and some food and water for<br>
myself.<br>
What a wonderful place this island is. So peaceful and void<br>
of any tourists with such tranquil sights and sounds it was<br>
awhile before I brought myself to disturb it with the<br>
slaughter of Willow Wisps.<br>
I found a single frolicking wisp and sent the pet to attack it<br>
while I would stand back and blast or heal or maybe even<br>
take a poke or two myself. The next thing I know there are<br>
three wisps, maybe four, and the slaughter disturbing the<br>
peace in the land turned out to be me and the pet wailing.<br>
Luckily I had the ability to bind myself to the pier on the<br>
island so I had not far to run to my body.<br>
Now I have a decision. I have just died with KEI how can I<br>
expect to survive without it? Do I take the long trip back,<br>
spend money I need, and admit my weakness or tough it<br>
out. Well I made a tough choice for a lad of 13 with KEI<br>
around every corner. I sucked it up and went back into the<br>
fray.<br>
This time I calmly searched out a safe spot and pulled one<br>
wisp to my new pet. &quot;This just might work,&quot; I say.<br>
----Cut to one Norrath week or so later----<br>
I now have 15 Greater Lightstones and dozens of victories<br>
under my belt. I have gotten to the point where I am tanking<br>
in order to need bandaging which raised my binding wound<br>
skill from 7 to 76. I have learned a tactic along the way:<br>
Cast longest reaching damage spell on lone mob to pull.<br>
Send earth pet to attack due to his root ability.<br>
Order pet to back off and follow me leaving mob in the distance to DD again.<br>
Send pet to attack, root, back off, follow me again while I med up a bit if needed.<br>
Repeat.<br>
This is really a tactic for tougher mobs but better to learn on<br>
dark blues right?<br>
By the end of the week I had no thoughts of KEI at all and<br>
have begun to learn the art of mana management and crowd<br>
control while soloing. Even dark blues can get quite tricky<br>
three at a time when you're young.<br>
It took being alone on a deserted island for a week for me to<br>
kick the mind candy but isn't that the way with any addiction?<br>
You have to hit some sort of bottom of you are just kidding<br>
yourself. When I came back to PoK to camp in a real bed<br>
there was shouts of &quot;Kei here&quot; and &quot;extended Kei there&quot;<br>
and I didn't even twitch. <br>
This was also a time of a lost Magician beginning to find his<br>
strengths and weaknesses and generally what it is to be a<br>
caster / summoner rather than melee class. I'm sure many<br>
of you remember the times when you first realized that the<br>
class you chose was just plain cool and began to enjoy<br>
Norrath so much more.<br>
<br>
--- uh oh ---<br>
<br>
Then just when I kick the habit Coddington mentions that<br>
KEI might help with trade skills such as tinkering.<br>
Gotta be strong, just say no, one day at a time.<br>
But if it's just to better myself it can't be such a bad thing right?<br>
As in life, the saga continues.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E8fA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bthearrowoflightcommons.showUserPublicProfile?gid=montagmccleaud>Montag McCleaud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer of Dragon Fodder</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#000080>(3/31/03 2:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bushwill clean but not sober</span><hr size=1> Brilliant, Just Brilliant.<br>
